Package: encryptor
Version: 2.0.0-1
Architecture: all
Maintainer: mpgamer75 <mpgamer75@github.com>
Depends: openssl (>= 1.1.0), bash (>= 4.0)
Recommends: curl, wget, git, coreutils, less
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://github.com/mpgamer75/encryptor
Description: |
 Advanced file encryption tool with modern symmetric algorithms
 Encryptor is a powerful, user-friendly command-line encryption tool that
 provides security for your files. Built with pure Bash and OpenSSL 3.x,
 it offers modern encryption algorithms with comprehensive certificate
 management and security auditing capabilities.
 .
 Features:
  - Modern symmetric ciphers: AES-256-CBC/CTR, ChaCha20, Camellia-256, ARIA-256
  - S/MIME certificate-based asymmetric encryption with AES-256-GCM
  - X.509 certificate management (Root CA, CSR generation, certificate signing)
  - Certificate tools: PKCS#12 export, validation, expiration checking
  - Security audit suite: local system checks and certificate analysis
  - testssl.sh integration for remote SSL/TLS server scanning
  - Interactive TUI with color-coded menus and file browser
  - Comprehensive logging and operation reporting
  - Secure file deletion with 3-pass overwrite option
  - PBKDF2 key derivation (100,000 iterations) for password-based encryption
  - Cross-platform compatibility (Linux, macOS, WSL)